  "prompt": "Are there any TV series similar to How to Get Away with Murder?",
  "response": "If you enjoyed \"How to Get Away with Murder,\" there are several other TV series that you might find interesting due to their suspenseful storytelling, complex characters, and legal or crime elements. Here are a few recommendations:\n\n1. **Scandal** - Created by Shonda Rhimes, this political thriller is intense and full of twists, focusing on crisis management and political intrigue.\n\n2. **Suits** - This legal drama centers on a talented college dropout who starts working at a prestigious law firm, dealing with legal cases while trying to keep his lack of a degree a secret.\n\n3. **The Good Wife** - Combining legal drama with personal intrigue, this series follows a woman who returns to her career in law after her husband's political scandal.\n\n4. **Damages** - A legal thriller with a non-linear narrative, it focuses on a ruthless lawyer and her prot\u00e9g\u00e9e, filled with suspense and unexpected turns.\n\n5. **The Undoing** - A psychological thriller featuring a series of unraveling secrets following a violent death, involving a high-profile therapist and her family.\n\n6. **Big Little Lies** - Although more focused on the lives of women in a wealthy community, it involves suspense and mystery around a murder investigation.\n\n7. **Breaking Bad** - While more of a crime drama, it has a similar tension and character complexity, following a chemistry teacher turned methamphetamine manufacturer.\n\n8. **Mindhunter** - A crime thriller that delves into the psychology of serial killers, offering sophisticated storytelling and character development.\n\n9. **Better Call Saul** - A prequel to \"Breaking Bad,\" it explores the making of a criminal lawyer, with plenty of legal drama and character dynamics.\n\nThese series share thematic elements with \"How to Get Away with Murder,\" such as complex legal issues, intricate plotlines, and morally ambiguous characters.",
